@startuml Sequence_Appointment_Booking

actor Customer
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB
actor Admin
actor Staff

== Customer Books Appointment ==

Customer -> Frontend: Login
Frontend -> API: POST /api/auth/login
API -> DB: Verify credentials
DB --> API: User data
API --> Frontend: Auth token

Customer -> Frontend: Book Appointment
Frontend -> Frontend: Fill appointment form\n(service, date, time)

Customer -> Frontend: Submit Appointment Request
Frontend -> API: POST /api/appointments\n(customerId, service, scheduledAt)
API -> DB: Create appointment\n(status = "Pending")
DB --> API: Appointment created

API -> DB: Create notification for admin
DB --> API: Notification created

API --> Frontend: Appointment request submitted
Frontend --> Customer: Confirmation message\n"Pending approval"

== Admin/Staff Approves Appointment ==

DB -> Admin: Notification: "New appointment request"

Admin -> Frontend: View Appointments
Frontend -> API: GET /api/appointments?status=Pending
API -> DB: Fetch pending appointments
DB --> API: Appointments list
API --> Frontend: Pending appointments
Frontend --> Admin: Display appointments

Admin -> Frontend: View Appointment Details
Frontend -> API: GET /api/appointments/:id
API -> DB: Fetch appointment
DB --> API: Appointment details
API --> Frontend: Appointment data
Frontend --> Admin: Appointment details

Admin -> Frontend: Approve Appointment
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/appointments/:id/approve\n(approved = true, approvedBy)
API -> DB: Update appointment\n(status = "Scheduled",\napproved = true,\napprovedBy = adminId)
DB --> API: Appointment updated

API -> DB: Create notification for customer
DB --> API: Notification created

API --> Frontend: Appointment approved
Frontend --> Admin: Success message

== Customer Receives Approval ==

DB -> Customer: Notification: "Appointment approved"

Customer -> Frontend: View Appointments
Frontend -> API: GET /api/appointments
API -> DB: Fetch customer appointments
DB --> API: Appointments (status = "Scheduled")
API --> Frontend: Appointments list
Frontend --> Customer: Display approved appointments

== Appointment Completed ==

Admin -> Frontend: Mark Appointment Complete
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/appointments/:id\n(status = "Completed")
API -> DB: Update appointment
DB --> API: Appointment updated

API --> Frontend: Appointment completed
Frontend --> Admin: Confirmation

note right of DB
  Appointment Status Flow:
  Pending → Scheduled → Completed
end note

@enduml


